<br>
Utility Value is calculated by totaling the the value of the different bonuses.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
<br>
Avernal Necklace<br>
19 con<br>
10 heat<br>
10 energy<br>
<br>
UV=(19*2/3)+(10*2)+(10*2)=52.7<br>
<br>
Utility Value is the best way to determine an item's value because it represents the usefulness of an item rather than how well it was spellcrafted (like imbue value).<br>
